Notes: The 'row_id' serves as a unique identifier for the prescription record, matching the 'hasCode' property which is used for unique coding in the ontology.
The 'patient_id' directly relates to the patient involved in the prescription, aligning with the 'hasPatient' relationship from the main entity.
The ATC code specifies the drug prescribed, mapped via the 'hasDrug' property, indicating the medication involved in the prescription.
The diagnosis code indicates the condition for which the drug is prescribed, fitting the 'hasIndicationToStart' relationship to Diagnosis.
The creation date represents a timestamp for the prescription record, mapped to the 'hasDateTime' property with the appropriate XML Schema datatype.
Number of times per day indicates frequency, mapped to 'hasFrequency' with Quantity datatype.
Dosage specifies the amount of drug administered, mapped via 'hasQuantity' to Quantity.
